Class GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:

@GridSpiInfo(author="GridGain Systems",
             url="www.gridgain.com",
             email="support@gridgain.com",
             version="4.0.0c.24032012")
@GridSpiMultipleInstancesSupport(value=true)
public class GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi
extends GridSpiAdapter
implements GridSwapSpaceSpi, GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpiMBean

LevelDB-based implementation of swap space SPI.

LevelDB is a fast key-value storage library written at Google, for more information see LevelDB Project.

Key-value pairs are stored in LevelDB instances on disk. Different swap eviction policies exist for removing unused data from storage whenever storage exceeds pre-configured maximum limit. The following eviction policies are available:

  • GridLevelDbEvictPolicy.EVICT_DISABLED - default policy. This is the most light-weight policy which allows for unlimited growth of swap space. When using this policy swap should be cleaned manually (e.g. during off-peak hours) to prevent unlimited growth.
  • GridLevelDbEvictPolicy.EVICT_OPTIMIZED_SMALL - with this policy the internal data structures are optimized for cases when stored values are small.
  • GridLevelDbEvictPolicy.EVICT_OPTIMIZED_LARGE - with this policy the internal data structures are optimized for cases when stored values are large.

Separate directories for LevelDB instances are created for each space under root folder configured via GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String). Spaces (and their directory structure) are initialized when the space is first used.

Every space has a name and when used in combination with data grid, space name represents the actual cache name associated with this swap space. Default name is null which is represented by GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.DFLT_SPACE_NAME.

Configuration

Mandatory

This SPI has no mandatory configuration parameters.

Optional SPI configuration.

  • Root folder path (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String)).
  • Root folder index range (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderIndexRange(int)).
  • Persistent (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setPersistent(boolean)).
  • Max swap count (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setDefaultMaxSwapCount(long)).
  • Max swap count map (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setMaxSwapCounts(Map)).
  • Count overflow ratio (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setEvictOverflowRatio(double)).
  • Eviction session frequency in milliseconds (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setEvictFrequency(long)).
  • Eviction policy (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setEvictPolicy(GridLevelDbEvictPolicy)).

Optional LevelDB parameters configuration.

For LevelDB configuration parameters explanation see LevelDB documentation.
  • LevelDb cache size (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setLevelDbCacheSize(long)).
  • LevelDB write buffer size (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setLevelDbWriteBufferSize(int)).
  • LevelDB block size (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setLevelDbBlockSize(int)).
  • LevelDB block paranoid checksums flag (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setLevelDbParanoidChecks(boolean)).
  • LevelDB block verify checksums flag (see GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setLevelDbVerifyChecksums(boolean)).

Java Example

GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi is configured by default and should be explicitly configured only if some SPI configuration parameters need to be overridden. 
 GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi spi = new GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi();

 // Configure root folder path.
 spi.setRootFolderPath("/path/to/swap/folder");

 // Set eviction policy.
 spi.setEvictPolicy(GridLevelDbEvictPolicy.EVICT_OPTIMIZED_SMALL);

 GridConfigurationAdapter cfg = new GridConfigurationAdapter();

 // Override default swap space SPI.
 cfg.setSwapSpaceSpi(spi);

 // Starts grid.
 G.start(cfg);

Spring Example

GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi can be configured from Spring XML configuration file: 
 <bean id="grid.cfg" class="org.gridgain.grid.GridConfigurationAdapter" scope="singleton">
     ...
     <property name="swapSpaceSpi">
         <bean class="org.gridgain.grid.spi.swapspace.leveldb.GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi">
             <property name="rootFolderPath" value="/path/to/swap/folder"/>
             <property name="evictPolicy" value="EVICT_OPTIMIZED_SMALL"/>
         </bean>
     </property>
     ...
 </bean>


For information about Spring framework visit www.springframework.org

DFLT_ROOT_FOLDER_PATH

public static final String DFLT_ROOT_FOLDER_PATH
Default directory path for swap files location. Grid name, node ID and index (only if necessary) will be appended to this path using dashes as separators.

If GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String) is not configured and GRIDGAIN_HOME system property is set, this folder will be created under GRIDGAIN_HOME.

If GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String) is not configured and GRIDGAIN_HOME system property is not set, this folder will be created under java.io.tmpdir.

@GridSpiConfiguration(optional=true)
public void setRootFolderIndexRange(int rootFolderIdxRange)
Sets root folder index range value.

If GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String) is not set and default path is locked (e.g. by other grid running on the same host) SPI will try next folder appending index to GRIDGAIN_HOME/GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.DFLT_ROOT_FOLDER_PATH. If GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String) is set, SPI tries to lock configured path only and this parameter is ignored.

If not provided, default value is GridLevelDbSwapSpaceSpi.DFLT_ROOT_FOLDER_IDX_RANGE.

Parameters:
rootFolderIdxRange - Root folder index range.
